        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 11 at 7:10PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 709 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Caddo, or 11 miles east of Breckenridge, moving northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Caddo and Ivan.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
